<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 8:30PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of south central Fergus
County through 900 PM MDT...
At 829 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Lewistown, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Giltedge, Heath and Forestgrove.
This includes Highway 200 between mile markers 84 and 103.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
